full_text: Reentry Permit I-551/I-15 316(a) 319(a) 50/20.35/15 I-215 in file U.S. Department of Justice OMB No. 1115-0062 Immigration and Naturalization Service Notice of Naturalization Oath Ceremony 630 Sansome Street, Room 233 San Francisco CA 94111 AR#: A12 797 485/mk Date: March 15, 2001 ANA MORONTA 18998 CARLTON AVE. CASTRO VALLEY CA 94546 CC: MAR 27 2001 You are hereby notified to appear for a Naturalization Oath Ceremony on: TUESDAY APRIL 10,2001 at: The Nob Hill Masonic Center Masonic Auditorium, First Floor 1111 California Street at Taylor Street San Francisco CA 94108 USE MUNI'S LINE 1, CALIFORNIA STREET OR POWELL STREET CABLE CAR, AND CONNECTIONS TO BAY AREA TRANSIT. PARKING IN THE CENTER IS LIMITED; TAKE THE ELEVATOR TO LEVEL 1. LOBBY DOORS OPEN AT 7:15 AM Please report promptly at 8:15 A.M., TABLE: 4 Allow a minimum of two (2) hours for the processing and the Oath Ceremony. You must bring the following with you: This letter, WITH ALL OF THE QUESTIONS ON THE OTHER SIDE ANSWERED IN INK OR ON A TYPEWRITER. Alien Registration Card. Reentry Permit, or Refugee Travel Document Any Immigration documents you may have. Bring TWO photos, 2"x 2" with your right EAR showing. Other : Proper attire should be worn. If you cannot come to this ceremony, return this notice immediately and state why you cannot appear. In such case, you will be sent another notice of ceremony at a later date. You must appear at an oath ceremony to complete the naturalization process. (SEE OTHER SIDE) Form N-445 (Rev. 01/08/92)
